HEADWORD: Distyle
<hw>Dis"tyle</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Gr. <grk>di-</grk> =
<grk>di`s-</grk> twice + <?/ pillar: cf. F. <ets>distyle</ets>.]</ety>
<fld>(Arch.)</fld> <def>Having two columns in front; -- said of a
temple, portico, or the like.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Distyle in antis</b></col>, <cd>having columns between
two ant⟦ae⟧. See <er>Anta</er>.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Disulphate</ent>⟦br⟧
